           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-17">People <supplied reason="subaudible">from the village of</supplied> Kāmaru B in the region of <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Khñuṁ Gho Kaṁvvan, Gho Kanteṅ, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanvvan, Tai Kaṁpur,
<gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁvrau, Tai Chke, Tai Krau, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Pit So, Tai Kanses, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Phnos, Lap Kaṁpit, Tai Utpala accompanied by 4 children, Tai Bhāva, Tai Kañchāy, <gap reason="lost"/>, another <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by 2 children, Tai Kaṁprvat accompanied by <gap reason="lost"/> children, <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by 4 children, Tai Bhadra, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, 2 male animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, Gho Kanloñ, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Chke, Gho Krau, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Sneha, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Laṅveṅ, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, another Gho kaṁvrau, Gho Kaṁpar, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Īśānaśiva, Gho Daiva Gho <gap reason="lost"/>;</p>
              <p n="17-18">group of Karpvis consisting of seven male and female laborers;</p>
              <p n="18-24">Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, 2 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, Gho Panlas, Gvāl Kaṁpit, <gap reason="lost"/> Vrahmaputra, another Gho Pādāgraśiva, Gho Pavitra, Gho Śivabheda, Gho Amr̥ta Khvas, Gho Kaṁpit, Gho Kandai, Gho Śivabhāva, Gho Kaṁbhat, Gho Dhavala, Gho Chke, Gho Khñuṁ, Gho Kaṁvis, Gho Kandhi;</p>
              <p n="24-25">group of Kandhi consisting of 12 male and female laborers;</p>
              <p n="25-32">Tai Kantvan, Tai Pan-u, Tai Kanteṅ Yvān, Tai Sārasvati; 6 slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>khñuṁ</foreign></supplied>, 15 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>. Total number of the people from the village of Kāmaru in the region of Ugrapura: 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si</foreign></supplied>, 106 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 16 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 70 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 16 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, 4 boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, 6 girls at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, 2 baby boys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, 12 baby girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, 10 children without names, 7 people from Kamvis, 12 people from Kandhi.</p>
